name: CloudScript

apiDescriptionList: API methods for executing CloudScript using an Entity Profile

properties.name: AttributedAt
properties.description: UTC time stamp of attribution

properties.name: CampaignId
properties.description: Attribution campaign identifier

properties.name: Platform
properties.description: Attribution network name

properties.name: EmailAddress
properties.description: The email address

properties.name: Name
properties.description: The name of the email info data

properties.name: VerificationStatus
properties.description: The verification status of the email

EntityKey.name: EntityKey
EntityKey.description: Combined entity type and ID structure which uniquely identifies a single entity.

properties.name: Id
properties.description: Unique ID of the entity.

properties.name: Type
properties.description: Entity type. See https://docs.microsoft.com/gaming/playfab/features/data/entities/available-built-in-entity-types

properties.name: TypeString
properties.description: Alternate name for Type.

properties.name: APIRequestsIssued
properties.description: Number of PlayFab API requests issued by the CloudScript function

properties.name: Error
properties.description: Information about the error, if any, that occurred during execution

properties.name: FunctionName
properties.description: The name of the function that executed

properties.name: FunctionResult
properties.description: The object returned from the CloudScript function, if any

properties.name: FunctionResultTooLarge
properties.description: Flag indicating if the FunctionResult was too large and was subsequently dropped from this event. This only occurs if the total event size is larger than 350KB.

properties.name: HttpRequestsIssued
properties.description: Number of external HTTP requests issued by the CloudScript function

properties.name: Logs
properties.description: Entries logged during the function execution. These include both entries logged in the function code using log.info() and log.error() and error entries for API and HTTP request failures.

properties.name: LogsTooLarge
properties.description: Flag indicating if the logs were too large and were subsequently dropped from this event. This only occurs if the total event size is larger than 350KB after the FunctionResult was removed.

properties.name: ProcessorTimeSeconds
properties.description: Processor time consumed while executing the function. This does not include time spent waiting on API calls or HTTP requests.

properties.name: Revision
properties.description: The revision of the CloudScript that executed

ExecuteEntityCloudScriptRequest.name: ExecuteEntityCloudScriptRequest
ExecuteEntityCloudScriptRequest.description: Executes CloudScript with the entity profile that is defined in the request.

properties.name: CustomTags
properties.description: The optional custom tags associated with the request (e.g. build number, external trace identifiers, etc.).

properties.name: Entity
properties.description: The entity to perform this action on.

properties.name: FunctionName
properties.description: The name of the CloudScript function to execute

properties.name: FunctionParameter
properties.description: Object that is passed in to the function as the first argument

properties.name: GeneratePlayStreamEvent
properties.description: Generate a 'entity_executed_cloudscript' PlayStream event containing the results of the function execution and other contextual information. This event will show up in the PlayStream debugger console for the player in Game Manager.

properties.name: RevisionSelection
properties.description: Option for which revision of the CloudScript to execute. 'Latest' executes the most recently created revision, 'Live' executes the current live, published revision, and 'Specific' executes the specified revision. The default value is 'Specific', if the SpecificRevision parameter is specified, otherwise it is 'Live'.

properties.name: SpecificRevision
properties.description: The specific revision to execute, when RevisionSelection is set to 'Specific'

ExecuteFunctionRequest.name: ExecuteFunctionRequest
ExecuteFunctionRequest.description: Executes an Azure Function with the profile of the entity that is defined in the request.

properties.name: CustomTags

properties.name: FunctionParameter
properties.description: Object that is passed in to the function as the FunctionArgument field of the FunctionExecutionContext data structure

properties.name: GeneratePlayStreamEvent
properties.description: Generate a 'entity_executed_cloudscript_function' PlayStream event containing the results of the function execution and other contextual information. This event will show up in the PlayStream debugger console for the player in Game Manager.

properties.description: Error from the CloudScript Azure Function.

properties.name: ExecutionTimeMilliseconds
properties.description: The amount of time the function took to execute

properties.name: FunctionResult
properties.description: The object returned from the function, if any

properties.name: FunctionResultTooLarge
properties.description: Flag indicating if the FunctionResult was too large and was subsequently dropped from this event.

properties.name: Error
properties.description: Error code, such as CloudScriptAzureFunctionsExecutionTimeLimitExceeded, CloudScriptAzureFunctionsArgumentSizeExceeded, CloudScriptAzureFunctionsReturnSizeExceeded or CloudScriptAzureFunctionsHTTPRequestError

properties.name: Message
properties.description: Details about the error

properties.name: StackTrace

calls.name: ExecuteEntityCloudScript
calls.summary: Cloud Script is one of PlayFab's most versatile features. It allows client code to request execution of any kind of custom server-side functionality you can implement, and it can be used in conjunction with virtually anything.
calls.requestDetails: Executes CloudScript with the entity profile that is defined in the request.

calls.name: ExecuteFunction
calls.summary: Cloud Script is one of PlayFab's most versatile features. It allows client code to request execution of any kind of custom server-side functionality you can implement, and it can be used in conjunction with virtually anything.
calls.requestDetails: Executes an Azure Function with the profile of the entity that is defined in the request.
